+# Patch Queue Layout
+
+`patches.d/` stores patch-runner queue artifacts.
+
+Directory names may vary by directory profile, but the semantic roles stay the same.
+
+## Directory Profiles
+
+| Role | Config key | Piscine | Sane | Terse |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| pending intake | `pending_dir` | `caught` | `pending` | `in` |
+| applied successfully | `applied_dir` | `purchased` | `applied` | `done` |
+| valid but failed to apply | `failed_dir` | `the_one_that_got_away` | `failed` | `fail` |
+| malformed artifact | `malformed_dir` | `garum_jar` | `malformed` | `bad` |
+| already applied | `overfished_dir` | `overfished` | `already_applied` | `dupe` |
+| intentionally skipped | `skipped_dir` | `catch_and_release` | `skipped` | `skip` |
+| runner scratch | `tmp_dir` | `.tmp` | `.tmp` | `.tmp` |
+
+## Rules
+
+Config keys are semantic and stable.
+
+Directory values may be piscine, sane, terse, or explicitly configured.
+
+Checklist status values should remain sober:
+
+- `applied`
+- `failed`
+- `malformed`
+- `already-applied`
+- `skipped`
+
+The scratch directory should be ignored by Git before the runner uses it.
